</p>
<p>With this, if you have a <code>User</code> object and call <code>getSubscription()</code> on it, you'll
get the <code>Subscription</code> object that's associated with this <code>User</code>, if there is one.</p>
<h2 id="prepping-the-account-page">Prepping the Account Page <a class="headerlink" href="user-has-subscription#prepping-the-account-page" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>And that's cool because we'll be able to fill in this fancy account page I created!
All this info: yep, it's just hardcoded right now. Open up the template for this page
at <code>app/Resources/views/profile/account.html.twig</code>. Instead of "None", add an <code>if</code>
statement: <code>if app.user</code> - that's the currently-logged-in user <code>app.user.subscription</code>,
then we know they have a Subscription. Add a label that says "Active". If they don't
have a subscription, say "None":</p>
