<p>Inside, start with <code>$subscription = $user-&gt;getSubscription()</code>. So, the user may <em>already</em>
have a row in the <code>subscription</code> table from a previous, expired subscription. If
they do, we'll just update that row instead of creating a second row. Every User
will have a <em>maximum</em> of one related row in the <code>subscription</code> table. It keeps things
simple.</p>
<p>But if they <em>don't</em> have a previous subscription, let's create one:
<code>$subscription = new Subscription()</code>. Then, <code>$subscription-&gt;setUser($user)</code>:</p>
